<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 17 日，星期三 05:13:29 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Cosmic Spring Chicken: Saturn's Rings Found to Be No Older Than 400 Million Years]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110411620" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105565/07/1055650746_0:0:1024:1024_1440x900_80_0_1_c2201431552270d5be6e6b0e2c908cb6.jpg?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1055650745" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/cosmic-spring-chicken-saturns-rings-found-to-be-no-older-than-400-million-years-1110411620.html?share-img=1055650745"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 照片：NASA/JPL-Caltech/Space Science Institute /</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">NASA 的卡西尼号宇宙飞船拍摄土星图像。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="NASA's Cassini spacecraft takes image of Saturn. - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="美国宇航局的卡西尼号宇宙飞船拍摄了土星的图像。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105565/07/1055650746_0:225:1024:801_1920x0_80_0_0_edd19bfdbed53c0b845dbdc44cf3db0b.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105565/07/1055650746_0:225:1024:801_640x0_80_0_0_06214e2a7af2a965313c5891f10c5cc3.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105565/07/1055650746_0:225:1024:801_1280x0_80_0_0_54cd170ab69fcf80827d64e393b3f5b6.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105565/07/1055650746_0:225:1024:801_1920x0_80_0_0_edd19bfdbed53c0b845dbdc44cf3db0b.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片 : NASA/JPL-Caltech/Space Science Institute / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">由科罗拉多大学博尔德分校的物理学家 Sascha Kempf 领导的新研究提供了令人信服的证据，证明土星环出奇地年轻，这有可能解开一个困扰研究人员一个多世纪的科学谜团。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">一项新的研究表明，土星环的年龄不超过 4 亿年，比官方估计的 45 亿岁的行星要年轻得多。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为了确定土星环的年龄，科学家们专注于研究尘埃的积累。他们观察到微小的岩石物质颗粒不断穿过太阳系，在行星体上留下一层薄薄的尘埃，包括构成土星环的冰。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">通过分析这个尘埃层形成的速度，研究人员能够估计环的年龄。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “把戒指想象成你家里的地毯，”肯普夫说。 “如果你铺了一张干净的地毯，你只需要等待。灰尘会落在你的地毯上。戒指也是如此。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110411620" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/cosmic-spring-chicken-saturns-rings-found-to-be-no-older-than-400-million-years-1110411620.html?share-block=1110411623" data-title="&amp;quot;Think about the rings like the carpet in your house,&amp;quot; Kempf said. &amp;quot;If you have a clean carpet laid out, you just have to wait. Dust will settle on your carpet. The same is true for the rings.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该团队分析了 2004 年至 2017 年美国宇航局卡西尼号宇宙飞船上的宇宙尘埃分析仪收集的数据，并检查了来自土星附近的 163 颗尘埃颗粒。尽管样本量相对较小，但他们的计算表明土星环可能只聚集了数亿年的尘埃，这意味着土星环是一种相对较新的宇宙现象。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该研究的发现揭示了土星环的年龄，但并未提供有关其形成的决定性答案。这些戒指的起源仍然未知，呈现出一个持续的科学谜题。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>长期以来，科学家们一直对土星环很感兴趣，这可以追溯到伽利略·伽利莱 (Galileo Galilei) 在 1610 年的观察。在 1800 年代，詹姆斯·克拉克·麦克斯韦 (James Clerk Maxwell) 推断土星环不是实心的，而是由许多单独的部分组成的。</p><p>土星环由七个不同的环带组成，这些环带由无数冰块组成，主要由纯水冰组成——其非凡的清洁度和微不足道的岩石物质让科学家们感到困惑。先前的假设认为土星环与土星同时形成，但这一观点引发了对土星环原始状态的质疑。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>此外，研究表明土星环可能正在消失。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国国家航空航天局的科学家此前曾报告说，冰正在逐渐下雨到地球上，并可能在大约 1 亿年内完全消失。在伽利略号和卡西尼号宇宙飞船可以观测到这些短暂特征的时期，它们的存在引发了关于它们形成的问题。一些科学家提出土星环可能起源于它的一颗卫星的引力破坏。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">肯普夫强调，在环仍然存在且充满活力的情况下目睹环是一种非凡的幸运，促使人们进一步调查它们的起源。该研究的结果提供了环年龄的结论，但给科学家们留下了更多的谜题有待解开。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究结果发表在<a href="https://dx.doi.org/10.1126/sciadv.adf8537" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">《科学进展》</a>杂志上。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 04:04:05 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/cosmic-spring-chicken-saturns-rings-found-to-be-no-older-than-400-million-years-1110411620.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/cosmic-spring-chicken-saturns-rings-found-to-be-no-older-than-400-million-years-1110411620.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>土星</category><category>美国宇航局</category><category>科罗拉多大学博尔德分校</category><category>空间</category><category>太空探索</category></item><item><title><![CDATA['I Haven't Been Gone': Feinstein Appears to Forget Her Near 3-Month Senate Absence]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110411301" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110411004_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_3035de197d93bac183e1b27f0b509900.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110410986" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/i-havent-been-gone-feinstein-appears-to-forget-her-near-3-month-senate-absence-1110411301.html?share-img=1110410986"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / J. Scott Applewhite</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">加利福尼亚州民主党参议员黛安·范斯坦 (Dianne Feinstein) 在缺席两个多月后重返参议院司法委员会，在助手的陪伴下</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Sen. Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif., is flanked by aides as she returns to the Senate Judiciary Committee following a more than two-month absence - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="加利福尼亚州民主党参议员黛安·范斯坦 (Dianne Feinstein) 在缺席两个多月后返回参议院司法委员会时，身边有助手陪同" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110411004_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_82ab2c6cfeaca71be53b04d00e11db78.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110411004_0:0:3072:1728_640x0_80_0_0_3884a0818c86b2c4f735f15b46ed7588.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110411004_0:0:3072:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_cb8a0be5b695f0d2395fa54b49201829.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110411004_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_82ab2c6cfeaca71be53b04d00e11db78.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © AP Photo / J. Scott Applewhite </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">这位 89 岁的参议员因带状疱疹感染导致她在 3 月份住院，缺席十周后于上周返回华盛顿。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">加利福尼亚州参议员黛安·范斯坦 (Dianne Feinstein) 刚结束近三个月的病假，周二似乎忘记了她在参议院大厅与两名记者进行了简短交谈。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为<a href="https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2023-05-16/feinstein-absence-senate-washington-health" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">两家不同</a><a href="https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2023/05/dianne-feinstein-health-return-to-senate.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">媒体</a>工作的记者证实了这个故事。两人说，他们看到费恩斯坦下了电梯，周围是工作人员，并被推上她自上周返回参议院以来一直使用的轮椅。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据报道，范斯坦在见到一位记者时说： <strong>“你不是一个急切的人吗？”</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">记者问她过得怎么样，这位议员说她“感觉很好。我的腿有问题。”记者随后问起她的腿怎么了，她拒绝回答，说这与别人无关，是她自己的事。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">到那时，谈话似乎很正常，即使有点对抗。但当记者问到她回来后参议院的同事对她说了些什么时，谈话发生了奇怪的转变。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “不，我没有离开，”这位今年错过了 50 多张选票的 89 岁参议员说。 “你应该跟着——我没有离开。我一直在工作。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110411301" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/i-havent-been-gone-feinstein-appears-to-forget-her-near-3-month-senate-absence-1110411301.html?share-block=1110411307" data-title="“No, I haven’t been gone,” the 89-year-old senator who has missed more than 50 votes this year said. “You should follow the—I haven’t been gone. I’ve been working.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">记者问她是否意味着她一直在家工作，但范斯坦坚称她一直在国会大厦。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “没有，我来过这里。我一直在投票。拜托，你要么知道，要么不知道。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110411301" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/i-havent-been-gone-feinstein-appears-to-forget-her-near-3-month-senate-absence-1110411301.html?share-block=1110411309" data-title="“No, I’ve been here. I’ve been voting. Please, you either know, or don’t know.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">范斯坦随后拒绝回答有关最近要求她辞职的问题，并被她的工作人员领了出去。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">虽然这位年迈的参议员可能指的是过去一周，当她回到华盛顿并在需要时对委员会进行投票时，似乎很难相信那些记得他们缺席数月的人会认为记者问的是最后一次一周而不是她最近长时间和有争议的缺席。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>记者还注意到，自从她上周返回以来，费恩斯坦在国会大厅里很难被发现。一位记者指出，费恩斯坦一直坚守在国会的人烟稀少的地区，并跳过午餐会和非紧急委员会会议。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">由于她的缺席，缺乏两党支持的多项司法任命被推迟；自她返回以来，这些任命进展迅速。 Feinstein 是参议院司法委员会的成员，尽管她在 2021 年放弃了委员会主席的职位。该委员会以 11-10 的比例支持民主党，没有 Feinstein 的选票，民主党别无选择，只能继续进行有一些人选的任命在等待范斯坦回归的同时获得共和党的支持。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">近年来，对费恩斯坦精神敏锐度的担忧一直在上升。一份报告援引匿名民主党盟友的话说，他们担心她没有履行参议员职责的心智能力。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在她回来后不久， <a href="https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/politics-features/dianne-feinstein-health-crisis-senate-resign-1234734590/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">一份报告</a>称这位参议员的精神状况迅速恶化，而工作人员则竭尽所能保持气氛或保持常态。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">一家美国媒体援引一名前工作人员和证实证人的话说，工作人员至少从 2019 年开始就使用一种系统来确保范斯坦永远不会被单独留在国会大厦。据报道，他们担心如果一名记者在无人看管的情况下与她交谈，并且在她离开办公室时随时准备一名工作人员陪伴她，她可能会说些什么。工作人员说范斯坦不知道这个系统。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>这位前职员和至少一名其他证人描述了在会议中范斯坦会忘记一次讨论的主题几分钟，迫使高级职员重新进行对话，就好像它是第一次发生一样，以安抚这位参议员。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">也有公共事件。 10 月，范斯坦在一份书面声明中宣布，她将自愿放弃临时总统的头衔，这使她成为总统职位的第三顺位继承人，仅次于副总统和众议院议长。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但当三周后有记者问起这件事时，她声称她仍在努力决定要做什么。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然后在 2 月，在宣布她将在任期结束时退休但继续留任后，一名记者在同一天询问了她这件事，范斯坦回答说她还没有做出决定。她的员工将混乱归咎于时间的混乱。 “哦，不，我没有宣布任何事情。有一天我会的，”范斯坦在宣布后一小时说。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 03:38:56 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/i-havent-been-gone-feinstein-appears-to-forget-her-near-3-month-senate-absence-1110411301.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/i-havent-been-gone-feinstein-appears-to-forget-her-near-3-month-senate-absence-1110411301.html<category>美洲</category><category>黛安·范斯坦</category><category>华盛顿</category><category>加州</category><category>参议院</category><category>美国参议院司法委员会</category><category>精神健康</category><category>精神状态</category><category>心智能力</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Report: EU Unlikely to Ban Pipeline Gas Imports From Russia in Next Sanctions Package]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110411161" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102452/20/1024522069_0:0:3058:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_1c92a44ff4ba62adad2def11f63e2f51.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1024522068" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/report-eu-unlikely-to-ban-pipeline-gas-imports-from-russia-in-next-sanctions-package-1110411161.html?share-img=1024522068"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Vladimir Sergeev /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">俄罗斯、欧盟、法国的旗帜和城市长廊上的尼斯徽章</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Flags of Russia, EU, France and coat of arms of Nice on the city's promenade - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="城市长廊上的俄罗斯、欧盟、法国国旗和尼斯徽章" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102452/20/1024522069_0:164:3058:1884_1920x0_80_0_0_8f4845d318da54747dc8a5fc23a41d76.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102452/20/1024522069_0:164:3058:1884_640x0_80_0_0_8453765ef2937b4f0588737a2a3e95ac.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102452/20/1024522069_0:164:3058:1884_1280x0_80_0_0_c316ac0b2d8b68d412fe0048ed944db0.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102452/20/1024522069_0:164:3058:1884_1920x0_80_0_0_8f4845d318da54747dc8a5fc23a41d76.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 弗拉基米尔·谢尔盖耶夫 /</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：据报道，欧盟不太可能在第 11 套制裁措施中禁止从俄罗斯进口管道天然气，因为这一想法在布鲁塞尔没有得到支持。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “据我所知，这不太可能通过，”一位来自去年俄罗斯天然气被切断的国家的欧盟外交官告诉美国媒体。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告称，尽管即将在日本广岛举行的七国集团 (G7) 峰会期间将讨论这个问题，但欧盟官员和分析人士表示，没有达成共识支持这一想法。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “依赖剩余天然气的国家的阻力太大了……第 11 轮制裁方案即将完成，此时采取这一巨大措施是行不通的，”这位外交官补充说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110411161" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/report-eu-unlikely-to-ban-pipeline-gas-imports-from-russia-in-next-sanctions-package-1110411161.html?share-block=1110411164" data-title="&quot;There is too much resistance from the countries dependent on the remaining gas ... The 11th sanctions package is almost done and inserting this huge measure at this moment is not going to work,&quot; the diplomat added. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">西方国家针对俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别军事行动以及对其他与莫斯科合作的国家施加压力，对俄罗斯实施制裁。他们还威胁要对涉嫌帮助莫斯科规避限制的国家实施二级制裁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 5 月初，欧盟委员会确认已向欧盟成员国发送了第 11 套俄罗斯制裁方案的提案。欧盟委员会主席乌尔苏拉·冯德莱恩明确指出，新一揽子计划将侧重于打击规避现有措施的行为。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 03:11:16 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/report-eu-unlikely-to-ban-pipeline-gas-imports-from-russia-in-next-sanctions-package-1110411161.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/report-eu-unlikely-to-ban-pipeline-gas-imports-from-russia-in-next-sanctions-package-1110411161.html<category>世界</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>欧盟 (EU)</category><category>布鲁塞尔</category><category>欧盟委员会</category><category>制裁</category><category>气体</category><category>气体供应</category><category>进口</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft Scientists Claim Glimmers of Human Logic Appearing in Neural Networks]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110410188" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_0:0:2031:675_1440x900_80_0_1_14fc333c8fe8eb7b95f3445c90739645.jpg?source-sid=cc_0" data-photoview-image-id="1080290189" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/microsoft-scientists-claims-glimmers-of-human-logic-appearing-in-neural-networks-1110410188.html?share-img=1080290189"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> //</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">人工智能</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_0" alt="Artificial intelligence - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="人工智能" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_1920x0_80_0_0_51ef4742040a93ff3ab674fce1642147.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_640x0_80_0_0_cf5c873ec33475c20051081e32f0a32a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_1280x0_80_0_0_fe4526570b82ef950870b5154659d6f6.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1b/1080290191_416:0:1616:675_1920x0_80_0_0_51ef4742040a93ff3ab674fce1642147.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">虽然围绕人工智能出现的新发现可能会彻底改变世界，但它们也不断引发人们对其可能对社会构成潜在危险的担忧。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">微软最近发表了一篇题为“通用人工智能的火花”的研究论文，探讨了与创造具有人类水平或更高智能的机器相关的可能性和风险。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">围绕<a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2303.12712.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">人工通用智能 (AGI)</a>概念的争论经常深入到哲学领域，使其成为计算机科学家之间有争议的话题。以前的 AGI 声明导致研究人员<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220612/google-engineer-claiming-ai-has-consciousness-placed-on-administrative-leave-report-details-1096232153.html" target="_blank">名誉受损</a>，并且区分真正的智能和模拟智能仍然是一个挑战。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，该领域最近的进展显示出希望，新的人工智能系统无需明确的编程即可产生类似人类的答案和想法。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">微软重组了其研究实验室，以包括专门研究 AGI 的小组，微软 AGI 论文的主要作者 Sébastien Bubeck 领导其中一个小组。他们正在使用的技术，OpenAI 的 GPT-4，被认为是目前可用的最强大的语言模型。微软已向 OpenAI 投资 130 亿美元，这表明两家公司之间的合作关系十分牢固。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>GPT-4 在分析了大量数字文本（包括书籍、文章和聊天记录）后，学会了生成自己的文本、写诗甚至参与对话。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员观察到该系统令人印象深刻的行为，展示了对人类概念和技能的“<strong>深刻而灵活的理解</strong>”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">例如，GPT-4 能够以押韵形式写出无限素数的数学证明，展示了数学和语言能力。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">当面临各种任务挑战时，GPT-4 展示了其分析、合成、评估和判断文本的能力，优于生成文本的能力。例如，它在被要求时生成了一个画独角兽的程序，甚至在删除相关代码后修改了程序以画出没有角的独角兽。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">它还编写了一个程序，根据个人信息评估糖尿病风险，并起草了一封支持电子作为圣雄甘地之声的美国总统候选人的信件，以及其他复杂的任务。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">批评者认为，微软的说法是没有根据的，代表了一种投机取巧的努力，以引起人们对一项在很大程度上仍被误解的技术的关注。一些研究人员强调，真正的通用智能需要对物理世界的理解，而这在理论上是 GPT-4 所不具备的。微软论文的主观性和非正式性，以及它背离严格的科学评估，进一步引起了专家们的怀疑。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">由于研究人员使用的 GPT-4 早期版本缺乏对不需要内容的微调，因此外部专家无法验证论文中的说法。微软澄清说，该系统的公共版本不如经过测试的版本强大。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">虽然 GPT-4 展示了类似于人类推理的能力，但它也表现出不一致的行为。一些专家认为，这些系统生成的文本可能无法反映真正的人类推理或常识。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">加州大学伯克利分校的心理学教授艾莉森·戈普尼克 (Alison Gopnik) 认为，将人工智能系统拟人化并在竞赛中将其与人类进行比较是一种不恰当的方法。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">对通用人工智能的追求继续吸引着研究人员，但关于这些系统产生的智能的真实性质和局限性的问题仍然存在。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 02:25:37 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/microsoft-scientists-claims-glimmers-of-human-logic-appearing-in-neural-networks-1110410188.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/microsoft-scientists-claims-glimmers-of-human-logic-appearing-in-neural-networks-1110410188.html<category>超越政治</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>开放人工智能</category><category>微软</category><category>人工智能</category><category>人工智能 (AI)</category><category>聊天GPT </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Over 900 People Evacuated From Italy's Emilia-Romagna Over Heavy Rains]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110410689" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:0:3076:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_6babe5064d3f4d0f5e9900eda018a445.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1036678931" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/over-900-people-evacuated-from-italys-emilia-romagna-over-heavy-rains-1110410689.html?share-img=1036678931"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Natalia Seliverstova /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">世界城市。罗马</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="World cities. Rome - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="世界城市。罗马" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_1920x0_80_0_0_961ca57cb3d956f4bef895b941666dbe.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_640x0_80_0_0_08aa116b1442e0429151b4605a0947e4.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_1280x0_80_0_0_fd09512964f4c3bd1d0f138b72824c7d.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103667/89/1036678932_0:160:3076:1890_1920x0_80_0_0_961ca57cb3d956f4bef895b941666dbe.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Natalia Seliverstova /</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据罗马（人造卫星）网报道：意大利媒体周二报道，由于暴雨，已有 900 多人从意大利北部的艾米利亚-罗马涅地区撤离。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在切塞纳市，萨维奥河决堤，导致建筑物一楼被洪水淹没。该市市长办公室禁止车辆通过当地的桥梁。据报道，该市的市民被要求离开建筑物的一楼。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据报道，博洛尼亚当局已敦促政府机构和公司允许员工在周三远程工作，届时该地区将保持最高级别的天气危险。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">佩萨罗市市长表示，由于 Genica 人工河道已经溢出，该市的情况非常危急。在摩德纳市，塞基亚河上的桥梁已经关闭。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">最紧张的局势发生在亚得里亚海沿岸的城市。港口城市西尼加利亚的市长敦促市民不要呆在建筑物的一楼。里乔内市的一个救护车部门已被洪水淹没，但仍继续运作了几个小时。一些人在被困在桥下的汽车中后寻求救援人员的帮助。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 5 月初，艾米利亚-罗马涅 (Emilia-Romagna) 的恶劣天气导致两人死亡，数百人因山体滑坡风险而被疏散。洪水还导致铁路交通中断。艾米利亚-罗马涅当局估计自然灾害造成的损失为 10 亿欧元（11 亿美元）。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 01:46:10 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/over-900-people-evacuated-from-italys-emilia-romagna-over-heavy-rains-1110410689.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/over-900-people-evacuated-from-italys-emilia-romagna-over-heavy-rains-1110410689.html<category>世界</category><category>意大利</category><category>疏散</category><category>洪水</category><category>洪水</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Chinese Embassy Slams Truss' Visit to Taiwan as 'Political Show']]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110410398" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:0:2948:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_fbb9bdd46fb7572d70a350cd218791d5.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1089828524" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html?share-img=1089828524"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Andy Wong</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">档案 - 在这张 2016 年 4 月 14 日的档案照片中，中国国旗飘扬在中国上海的写字楼上</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="FILE - In this April 14, 2016 file photo, a Chinese national flag flutters against the office buildings in Shanghai, China - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="文件 - 在这张 2016 年 4 月 14 日的文件照片中，中国国旗飘扬在中国上海的写字楼上" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_1920x0_80_0_0_25043da799fc5cb3e61c7aec9c65f5ea.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_640x0_80_0_0_1b514984decb15336628291094a53778.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_1280x0_80_0_0_ea5b490d743de644d89aada408bf7d40.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0a/0b/1089828528_0:279:2948:1937_1920x0_80_0_0_25043da799fc5cb3e61c7aec9c65f5ea.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Andy Wong </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：中国驻伦敦大使馆周二反对英国前首相特拉斯访问台湾，称其为“政治秀”。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">大使馆在网站上说：“英国政客利兹特拉斯最近访问台湾是一场危险的政治秀，只会对英国造成伤害。” “这一挑衅举动已引起中国人民的强烈愤慨，将受到各界有良知人士的坚决拒绝。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">大使馆补充<strong>说，“当前对台海和平的最大威胁是‘台独’活动和外国势力对‘台独’的纵容和支持。”</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “特拉斯等人打‘台湾牌’，搞政治秀，与‘台独’分裂势力勾结，挑起台海对抗，加剧台海紧张局势，其险恶用心充分暴露。”声明中写道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110410398" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html?share-block=1110410401" data-title="&quot;By playing the 'Taiwan card' and engaging in political shows, Truss and the like are colluding with the 'Taiwan independence' secessionist forces to provoke confrontation and escalate tensions across the Taiwan Strait. What they did has fully revealed their sinister intentions,&quot; the statement read. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周二早些时候，台湾媒体报道特拉斯抵达桃园国际机场，受到台湾外交部长吴钊燮的欢迎。预计她将于周三早些时候在台北发表题为“台湾：在自由与民主的前线”的演讲。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特拉斯上周宣布了她的访问。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">上周，英国议会下议院外交事务委员会主席严厉批评特拉斯访问台湾的决定，并称此行是 Instagram 的“表演性”和“最糟糕的”外交（因极端主义在俄罗斯被禁止），警告正如《卫报》援引的那样，这可能会导致该地区的局势严重升级，就像 2022 年 8 月时任美国众议院议长南希·佩洛西 (Nancy Pelosi) 访问台湾之后发生的那样。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>台湾自 1949 年以来一直独立于中国大陆，被北京视为其省份，而拥有自己的民选政府的台北则坚称自己是一个自治国家，但并未宣布独立。</p><p>北京反对外国与台北进行任何官方接触，并认为中国对该岛的主权无可争辩。</p></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 01:31:57 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/chinese-embassy-slams-truss-visit-to-taiwan-as-political-show-1110410398.html<category>亚洲</category><category>利兹桁架</category><category>吴约瑟</category><category>台湾海峡</category><category>台北</category><category>南希·佩洛西</category><category>中国大使馆</category><category>政治裂痕</category></item></channel></rss>